  "text": "Winn studied the relation between tobacco usage and oral diseases and concluded that tobacco use is an important risk factor for oral cancer, mucosal lesions, periodontal diseases, delayed healing after periodontal treatment, gingival recession, and root and crown caries [CITATION_1] . Available evidences declare that the risk of oral diseases is rising with tobacco consumption while withdrawal can reduce the risk. The high impact of tobacco use on oral diseases has also been proved [CITATION_2] .",
